excerpt: Grand, bustling public market from 1912 featuring vendors for meat, produce, bread & hot food.
detail_description: West Side Market, established in 1912, is a vibrant and historic public market offering a wide array of goods such as meat, produce, bread, and hot food. The market originally had 109 stalls with additional storage added later. Many of the stalls are still operated by families who have been there since its opening, while others are run by vendors from various parts of the world.
name: West Side Market

excerpt: Iconic music-minded museum loaded with pop-culture memorabilia, artifacts, instruments & a jukebox.
detail_description: The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame is a museum dedicated to the history of rock and roll. It features displays on the music, the performers, and the industry. The museum is located in Cleveland, Ohio.
name: Rock & Roll Hall of Fame

excerpt: Museum featuring over 45,000 works covering 6,000 years plus films, music, lectures & a restaurant.
detail_description: The Cleveland Museum of Art, established in 1916, is a popular destination in Ohio, attracting over half a billion visitors annually. The museum boasts an impressive collection of nearly 45,000 artifacts spanning 6,000 years. Its exhibits are elegantly displayed in chronological order, showcasing the evolution of renowned artists throughout history. Additionally, the museum offers a special play area for children and hosts various events and exhibits.
name: The Cleveland Museum of Art

excerpt: House used in "A Christmas Story" film, now a museum with a replicated interior & film memorabilia.
detail_description: The House from A Christmas Story, located in Cleveland, Ohio, is a 19th-century Victorian home that was used for exterior shots in the classic Christmas movie. It has been transformed into a museum and cafe where visitors can explore the replicated interior and view film memorabilia. The house offers fans of the movie an opportunity to step inside Ralphie's iconic home and relive favorite moments from the film.
name: House from A Christmas Story

excerpt: Animal exhibits, a simulated rainforest, an interactive kids section, a gift shop & restaurants.
detail_description: Cleveland Metroparks Zoo is a sprawling wildlife sanctuary with over 3,000 animals from 600 species. The zoo offers interactive experiences like giraffe and lorikeet feedings, camel rides, and overnight programs in safari tents. Visitors can explore distinct areas of the zoo featuring favorites such as Elephant Crossing and a carousel. Despite its location near downtown Cleveland, the hilly landscape creates an immersive experience away from the city's industrial surroundings.
name: Cleveland Metroparks Zoo

excerpt: All-seasons living museum with a greenhouse, a conservatory, outdoor gardens & an education center.
detail_description: Nestled in the University Circle near other cultural attractions, Cleveland Botanical Garden is a captivating all-seasons living museum spanning 10 acres. The Eleanor Armstrong Smith Glasshouse is a highlight, featuring peculiar desert and rainforest plants alongside hundreds of butterflies, birds, and reptiles. Families can also explore the Hershey Children's Garden for nature play activities. The garden boasts diverse landscapes including herb, Japanese, rose, and topiary gardens as well as a greenhouse and conservatory.
name: Cleveland Botanical Garden

excerpt: Tranquil burial place of billionaire John D. Rockefeller & former president James A. Garfield.
detail_description: Lake View Cemetery, established in 1869, is a serene burial ground that also serves as a picturesque destination for visitors. The landscape features stunning gardens inspired by European designs and offers dramatic views, winding pathways, and historic structures. Notable attractions include the James A. Garfield Memorial, Wade Memorial Chapel, the Haserot angel sculpture, and Daffodil Hill in spring. This tranquil setting provides an opportunity to connect with nature and beauty while paying homage to prominent figures like billionaire John D.
name: Lake View Cemetery

excerpt: Kid-friendly venue with interactive exhibits, plus a giant-screen movie theater & steamship tours.
detail_description: Great Lakes Science Center is a must-visit, family-friendly venue in Downtown Cleveland. It offers interactive exhibits, a giant-screen movie theater, and steamship tours. The Science Store in the main lobby is accessible without paying admission and features astronaut ice cream, NASA apparel, STEM gifts, and solar eclipse safety glasses. The center was a finalist for Best Science Museum in the 2022 USA Today 10Best Readers Choice travel award contest.
name: Great Lakes Science Center

excerpt: Planetarium & museum focusing on local prehistoric discoveries, fossils & geological specimens.
detail_description: The Cleveland Museum of Natural History is a treasure trove for anyone fascinated by the wonders of our planet. Nestled just five miles from downtown Cleveland in University Circle, this museum has been captivating visitors since its inception in 1920. With an exciting array of offerings including immersive 3D films and engaging planetarium shows, it caters to science enthusiasts of all ages. The museum is currently undergoing a remarkable $150 million renovation that aims to enhance its facilities and exhibits significantly.
name: Cleveland Museum of Natural History
address: 1 Wade Oval Dr, Cleveland, OH 44106, USA

excerpt: Open for tours from May 1 to September 30, this World War II-era sub honors fallen submariners.
detail_description: The USS Cod Submarine Memorial in Cleveland, Ohio is a World War II-era submarine that pays tribute to fallen submariners. It is open for tours from May 1 to September 30 and is listed as one of the area's National Historic Landmarks. The submarine is maintained in its original condition, allowing visitors to experience its history firsthand by using the original hatchways and ladders during their tour.
name: USS Cod Submarine Memorial
address: 1201 N Marginal Rd, Cleveland, OH 44114, USA

excerpt: Interactive marine exhibits, including a walk-through experience & a mock research vessel.
detail_description: The Greater Cleveland Aquarium offers an immersive experience for visitors of all ages, with over fifty exhibits spread across eight galleries. Children can enjoy interactive marine displays, including a walk-through experience and a mock research vessel. The Touch Pool in the Coastal Boardwalk gallery allows kids to come face to face with and touch stingrays, while older children can be surrounded by sharks and other sea creatures in the underwater Sea Tube.
name: Greater Cleveland Aquarium

excerpt: Contemporary art, educational programs & performances presented in an edgy steel-paneled structure.
detail_description: The Museum of Contemporary Art Cleveland, also known as moCa, stands out with its ever-changing exhibitions from present-day artists. The museum's edgy steel-paneled structure houses thought-provoking and dynamic displays that celebrate modern art in all its forms. In addition to showcasing over 2,000 artists, moCa offers educational programs and performances within its unique architectural setting. Visitors can expect a refreshing experience with each visit as they explore the diverse range of contemporary works on display.
name: Museum of Contemporary Art Cleveland

excerpt: Performing arts center for Broadway-style shows, concerts, dance productions, plays, comedy & opera.
detail_description: Playhouse Square is a vibrant performing arts center that serves as the heartbeat of Cleveland's cultural scene. This stunning venue hosts an array of Broadway-style shows, concerts, dance performances, plays, comedy acts, and operas. As you explore the city on a delightful tour that includes local markets and bakeries, you'll have the chance to visit Playhouse Square along with other iconic sights like Edgewater Park and University Circle.
name: Playhouse Square

excerpt: Park on Lake Erie featuring a yacht club, beaches, a fishing pier, picnic areas & more.
detail_description: Edgewater Park is a picturesque park located on the shores of Lake Erie, forming part of the Cleveland Metroparks Lakefront Reservation. It boasts 9,000 feet of shoreline and features attractions such as Edgewater Beach, Perkins Beach, a Marina and Yacht Club. The park offers various activities including biking, boating, paddle sports, picnicking and fishing. Visitors can also enjoy amenities like picnic tables, restrooms and trail access.
name: Edgewater Park

excerpt: Cleveland Guardians home field with a mezzanine-level kids' club, concessions & youth workshops.
detail_description: Progressive Field, the vibrant home of the Cleveland Guardians, is a fantastic destination for families and baseball enthusiasts alike. This impressive stadium not only accommodates over 35,000 fans but also features a delightful Family Deck designed specifically for parents and their little ones. Here, you'll find an inviting lounge area alongside family-friendly concessions and the Kids Clubhouseâ€”an interactive space brimming with engaging activities to keep children entertained.
name: Progressive Field

excerpt: University Circle is a busy cultural hub with institutions like the Cleveland Natural History Museum and the Museum of Contemporary Art, a modern mirrored structure with regularly changing exhibitions. Severance Hall hosts performances by the Cleveland Orchestra, and paths wind past roses and maple trees at the Cleveland Botanical Garden. Casual college bars, ramen joints and Asian fusion eateries dot the area.
detail_description: University Circle is a vibrant cultural district in Cleveland, featuring renowned institutions like the Cleveland Natural History Museum and the Museum of Contemporary Art. The area also boasts Severance Hall, where visitors can enjoy performances by the Cleveland Orchestra. Additionally, the Cleveland Botanical Garden offers serene paths surrounded by roses and maple trees. University Circle is also home to various dining options, including casual college bars, ramen joints, and Asian fusion eateries.
name: University Circle

excerpt: Soaring, ornate indoor mall, opened in 1890, today housing the Hyatt hotel, shops & restaurants.
detail_description: The Arcade, also known as the Old Arcade, is a magnificent indoor mall in downtown Cleveland that opened its doors in 1890. It holds the distinction of being America's first indoor shopping center and was financed by prominent businessmen including John D. Rockefeller. The design of the Arcade was inspired by Milan's Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II and it is often referred to as the Crystal Palace. In addition to housing shops and restaurants, it also accommodates the Hyatt hotel.
name: The Arcade

excerpt: Large landscaped city plaza with a memorial, a splash pad, a seasonal skating rink & food trucks.
detail_description: Cleveland Public Square is a spacious urban plaza featuring a variety of attractions. It includes a memorial, splash pad, seasonal skating rink, and food trucks. The square gained fame as the filming location for a scene in The Avengers movie, where it was transformed into a German city with Loki commanding terrified extras. Visitors to Cleveland will find the city easy to navigate with clear signage and grid layouts.
name: Cleveland Public Square
address: 50 Public Square Suite 1910, Cleveland, OH 44113, USA

excerpt: This museum in the Burke Lakefront Airport chronicles the history of women in aviation & space.
detail_description: The International Womenâ€™s Air & Space Museum, located at Burke Lakefront Airport in Cleveland, Ohio, is a tribute to the remarkable achievements of women in aviation and space exploration. Founded in 1986 by aviator Bernice Steadman, the museum relocated to its current site in 1998. It offers free daily admission and houses extensive collections of artifacts related to female pioneers such as Amelia Earhart and Ruby Wine Sheldon.
name: International Womenâ€™s Air & Space Museum
address: 1501 N Marginal Rd, Cleveland, OH 44114, USA

excerpt: The Flats is a redeveloped area on the banks of the Cuyahoga River, known for its happening nightlife, with edgy bars and clubs hosting live music, comedy and drag shows. The party vibe extends to patios and beer gardens nearby, while dining options include gourmet taco joints and hip cafes. A popular walkway lines the west bank of the waterfront, and water taxis take people from one side of the river to the other.
detail_description: The Flats is a revitalized area along the Cuyahoga River, offering a vibrant nightlife scene with trendy bars and clubs featuring live entertainment. Visitors can enjoy various dining options including gourmet taco spots and stylish cafes. The west bank of the waterfront boasts a popular walkway, while water taxis provide convenient transportation across the river. This district has undergone significant urban renewal, transforming former industrial zones into an entertainment-focused waterfront section and introducing new sports stadiums to the city.
name: The Flats

excerpt: Cleveland is a city in the U.S. state of Ohio and the county seat of Cuyahoga County. Located along the southern shore of Lake Erie, it is situated across the Canadaâ€“U.S. maritime border and approximately 60 mi west of the Ohio-Pennsylvania state border. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Cleveland, a city in Ohio, is located on the southern shore of Lake Erie and is known for its annual -X Indoor Amusement Park that offers fair food and thrilling rides. The park has become a tradition in northeastern Ohio, drawing visitors to enjoy the unique country fair experience. Additionally, Cleveland is home to Brookside Reservation, a Cleveland Metropark featuring athletic fields and the Cleveland Metroparks Zoo. The reservation offers the 2.
name: Cleveland

excerpt: In Little Italy, the main strip Mayfield Road is full of old-school Italian cafes, bakeries and pizzerias, as well as elegant trattorias where singers perform opera arias. Indie art galleries and Italian food and wine shops are also dotted around the area. Colorful murals depict the stories of Italian immigrants, while the Garfield Monument in Lake View Cemetery marks the burial site of the 20th US president.
detail_description: Little Italy in Cleveland is a vibrant neighborhood filled with old-school Italian cafes, bakeries, and pizzerias along Mayfield Road. The area also boasts elegant trattorias featuring opera performances, indie art galleries, and Italian food and wine shops. Colorful murals depicting the stories of Italian immigrants add to the neighborhood's charm. Additionally, visitors can explore the Garfield Monument at Lake View Cemetery, marking the burial site of the 20th US president.
name: Little Italy

excerpt: Iconic microbrewery with house suds, an updated American menu, free tours & a patio.
detail_description: Great Lakes Brewing Company is a renowned microbrewery in Ohio City, offering house suds and an updated American menu. The brewery's store provides a variety of traditional items, making it a great spot for last-minute gift shopping. In addition to its brewpub and seven-barrel brewhouse, the company has become a Cleveland landmark with its all-wood interior and home-grown beer.
name: Great Lakes Brewing Company

excerpt: Unique collection of city gardens commemorating different ethnic groups with diverse landscapes.
detail_description: The Cleveland Cultural Gardens is a remarkable collection of over 30 individual botanical gardens, each representing the diverse ethnic populations of the city. Originally established in 1916 as a Shakespeare Garden, it was transformed into ethnic-focused gardens in 1926 to honor various cultural groups following a suggestion by Leo Weidenthal. These gardens now pay tribute to African-American and indigenous populations, as well as specific countries from Europe, Asia, and the Middle East.
name: Cleveland Cultural Gardens

excerpt: Museum on a 618-ft. docked 1925 Great Lakes freighter steamship, with interactive exhibits.
detail_description: Nestled along the shores of Lake Erie, the Steamship William G. Mather Museum offers a unique glimpse into maritime history aboard a beautifully restored 618-foot freighter that dates back to 1925. Once a vital part of the Cleveland-Cliffs Steamship Company fleet, this historic vessel played an essential role in shaping northeast Ohio's industrial landscape.
name: Steamship William G. Mather Museum

excerpt: Gaming venue with slots, table games, live music & several restaurants, including a buffet.
detail_description: Nestled in the iconic Higbee Building in Public Square, Jack Cleveland Casino is a vibrant gaming destination that promises an unforgettable night out. Spanning over 100,000 square feet, this lively venue features an impressive array of entertainment options including more than 500 slot machines and 100 table games, alongside 30 poker tables for those looking to test their skills.
name: JACK Cleveland Casino

excerpt: Contemporary art & photography museum, plus events, in an expanded 1924 railroad substation.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Ohio City neighborhood, Transformer Station is a unique contemporary art and photography museum that breathes new life into a historic 1924 railroad substation. Originally built to power the Detroit Avenue Streetcar Line, this architectural gem has been transformed into a cultural hub since its renovation in 2010. Open to the public from Wednesday to Sunday, it offers free access to an array of exhibitions featuring both emerging and mid-career artists with a strong focus on photography and social justice themes.
name: Transformer Station

excerpt: Arty, residential Tremont has gourmet sandwich bars and craft coffee shops amid restored Victorian homes, with hip galleries showcasing local talent and boutiques stocking clothes by edgy young designers. Local landmarks include the striking Slavic-style church, St. Theodosius Russian Orthodox Cathedral, and a museum dedicated to the 1980s movie "A Christmas Story House."
detail_description: Tremont, a charming neighborhood in Cleveland, is known for its artistic vibe and residential feel. The area boasts gourmet sandwich bars, craft coffee shops, and trendy galleries set amidst beautifully restored Victorian homes. Visitors can explore local landmarks such as the stunning St. Theodosius Russian Orthodox Cathedral and the museum dedicated to the iconic 1980s movie 'A Christmas Story House.'
name: Tremont

excerpt: Picturesque garden with a greenhouse showcasing floral displays & exotic & native plant collections.
detail_description: Nestled within the Rockefeller Park, the Rockefeller Park & Greenhouse (RPG) offers a serene escape in the heart of Cleveland. The park features 26 nationality gardens, each adorned with statues, fountains, and bridges that make for a unique and picturesque setting. Visitors can stroll through scenic trails, have a picnic in designated areas, or explore the Cleveland Cultural Gardens within the park.
name: Rockefeller Park & Greenhouse

excerpt: Iconic home to the large outdoor sculpture "Free Stamp" by Claes Oldenburg & Coosje van Bruggen.
detail_description: Willard Park, located in downtown Cleveland, Ohio, is a must-see landmark for visitors. The park is home to the impressive 49-foot rubber stamp sculpture "Free Stamp" by Claes Oldenburg & Coosje van Bruggen. Situated near the Rock & Roll Hall of Fame and the Cleveland Science Center, it's a convenient stop on your way to other attractions. Named after painter Archibald Willard, the park also houses the original Cleveland Fire Fighters Memorial.
name: Willard Park
address: Lakeside Avenue East &, E 9th St, Cleveland, OH, USA

excerpt: A family-oriented venue with interactive exhibits designed to foster playful learning.
detail_description: The Children's Museum of Cleveland is a family-friendly destination featuring interactive exhibits aimed at promoting fun learning experiences for children. Recently relocated to a larger space, the museum now offers additional play and learning areas, as well as an outdoor picnic area. Highlights include Adventure City, where kids can engage in various activities while learning about daily life, and the engaging Wonder Lab with water tables for hours of entertainment.
name: The Children's Museum of Cleveland

excerpt: Petite, man-made park with artistic landscaping & an outdoor festival stage, plus Lake Erie views.
detail_description: Voinovich Bicentennial Park is a charming, man-made park offering artistic landscaping and a festival stage with stunning views of Lake Erie. Nestled in Cleveland, it's an ideal escape from the city's hustle and bustle. Spanning over four acres, the park provides various leisure opportunities such as volleyball, bocce, and fishing. In summer, visitors can enjoy outdoor concerts by the lake.
name: Voinovich Bicentennial Park
address: 800 E 9th Street Pier, Cleveland, OH 44114, USA

detail_description: Edgewater Beach, located just west of downtown Cleveland, is a popular destination for locals and visitors alike. Situated within the expansive Edgewater Park on Lake Erie, this beach offers 1000 feet of swimming access and even has a dog-friendly section. With amenities such as ample parking, concessions including cocktails and beer at the Edgewater Beach House, and space for gatherings with family and friends, it's an ideal spot for a summer afternoon.
name: Edgewater Beach

excerpt: Ohio City is a trendy dining and entertainment hub centered on the main strip of West 25th Street, with high-end cocktail bars and beer gardens, alongside fashionable vegan bistros and gourmet farm-to-table restaurants. West Side Market has stalls for specialty foods like smoked meats, baked goods and handmade ice-cream, while indie craft stores and galleries line side streets near the neoclassical Carnegie Library.
detail_description: Ohio City, a trendy neighborhood in Cleveland, is known for its vibrant dining and entertainment scene. The main strip of West 25th Street features high-end cocktail bars, beer gardens, vegan bistros, and farm-to-table restaurants. The iconic West Side Market offers specialty foods like smoked meats and handmade ice cream. This hipster-feeling neighborhood is rich in history with beautiful old homes and was once an independent city before being incorporated into Cleveland in 1854.
name: Ohio City

detail_description: Superelectric Pinball Parlor, situated in the vibrant Gordon Square Arts District of Cleveland, is a throwback to the 1970s and 1980s with its collection of over 20 classic arcade machines. The retro ambiance, complete with neon lights and vintage decor, offers a nostalgic trip down memory lane. Additionally, visitors can enjoy craft beer and cocktails at the bar while playing games.
name: Superelectric Pinball Parlor

detail_description: Cleveland Metroparks is a network of 18 interconnected parks offering various outdoor activities such as hiking, biking, golfing, water sports, and fishing. The well-marked trails make it easy for visitors to explore the green spaces and enjoy short hikes while observing wildlife like chipmunks, squirrels, and deer. It's also a great spot for photography with its picturesque sights. The park offers a peaceful and serene environment where visitors can find solitude and connect with nature.
name: Cleveland Metroparks
address: 1969 W Ridgewood Dr, Cleveland, OH 44134, USA

name: Public Square
address: 36 W Superior Ave, Cleveland, OH 44113, USA

excerpt: Woodland park split by the Rocky River, offering hiking trails with bird & deer sightings.
detail_description: Rocky River Reservation is a woodland park that spans across several communities from Berea to Rocky River. It offers hiking trails with opportunities to spot birds and deer. One of its main attractions is the Fort Hill Loop Trail, which covers 1.3 miles and includes the challenging Fort Hill Stairs with 155 steps, rewarding hikers with breathtaking panoramic views of the Rocky River. The trail also holds historical significance, featuring 2,000-year-old earthen walls built by early woodland tribes.
name: Rocky River Reservation
address: Valley Pkwy, North Olmsted, OH 44070, USA

excerpt: Established in 1869, this library offers a big collection of books & movies, plus events & classes.
detail_description: The Cleveland Public Library, established in 1869, is a grand institution with a rich history. The main branch, completed in 1925 by Walker & Weeks and expanded with the Louis Stokes Wing in 1997 by Hardy Holzman Pfeiffer Associates, stands as a testament to knowledge and learning. Often referred to as 'the Peoples University,' it boasts striking Corinthian columns and Italian Renaissance-style marble staircases.
name: Cleveland Public Library

excerpt: Opened in 1925, this airport features suspended sculptures that look like paper airplanes.
detail_description: Cleveland Hopkins International Airport, which first opened in 1925, is known for its unique suspended sculptures resembling paper airplanes. The Westin Cleveland hotel offers a convenient location within walking distance to attractions like the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame and sports stadiums. With 484 rooms, it provides various amenities including a fitness center, local artwork displays, and a farm-to-table steakhouse restaurant.
name: Cleveland Hopkins International Airport

detail_description: Nestled along the waterfront, Lakewood Park's Solstice Steps have emerged as a beloved destination for both locals and visitors alike. This stunning staircase offers an enchanting experience, especially during the warmer months when you can bask in breathtaking views of sunsets over Lake Erie. Known affectionately as Cleveland's outdoor living room, it provides a picturesque backdrop for memorable moments like proposals or simply enjoying the serene beauty of nature.
name: Solstice Steps

excerpt: Sizable museum housing an ample collection of antique cars, aircraft, carriages & other artifacts.
detail_description: The Crawford Auto Aviation Museum is a world-renowned museum housing an extensive collection of antique cars, aircraft, carriages, and other artifacts from across history. This facility is known for its rich automotive and aviation history as well as for its stellar collections of early Cleveland-made autos.
name: Crawford Auto Aviation Museum

detail_description: Cedar Point is the ultimate family-friendly destination, offering a delightful mix of activities that cater to all ages. Known as the roller coaster capital of the world, this iconic park boasts an impressive lineup of 18 thrilling coasters that will satisfy even the most daring adventurers. But itâ€™s not just about adrenaline; Cedar Point also features charming kids' areas, delicious dining options, and live entertainment that keeps everyone engaged.
name: Cedar Point

detail_description: Gordon Square Arts District in Cleveland is a vibrant and revitalized area that has become a popular residential and commercial arts district. It is home to prominent performing arts venues such as Cleveland Public Theatre, Near West Theatre, and Dobama Theatre. The district offers a range of cultural experiences, from well-known productions to new and adventurous works. Visitors can also explore independent galleries, shops, and the colorful Superelectric Pinball Parlor for an entertaining evening out.
name: Gordon Square Arts District

detail_description: The Cleveland Orchestra, established in 1918, is part of the prestigious Big Five orchestras in the United States. Their home base is the stunning Severance Hall, where they perform during the school year and at Blossom Music Center during summer. The orchestra also embarks on tours and residencies worldwide and can be heard on weekly radio broadcasts. In addition to their performances, Severance Hall offers educational programs, community initiatives, special events, and rental opportunities.
name: The Cleveland Orchestra

excerpt: Supermarket chain with departments for meat, produce, deli & bakery, plus wellness items & wine.
detail_description: Heinen's Grocery Store is a supermarket chain located in the historic Cleveland Trust Co. building in Downtown Cleveland. The building, dating back to 1907, boasts a mix of Beaux-Arts, Neoclassical, and Renaissance Revival architectural styles. Visitors can admire the stunning glass dome in the Rotunda and enjoy affordable wine and beer tasting on the second floor. The store offers departments for meat, produce, deli, bakery items, wellness products, and more.
name: Heinen's Grocery Store

excerpt: Large indoor venue for pro sports such as hockey, basketball & arena football plus various concerts.
detail_description: Rocket Mortgage FieldHouse stands as a premier indoor venue in Cleveland, hosting an array of professional sports and entertainment events. Home to the NBA's Cleveland Cavaliers and the AHL's Cleveland Monsters, this vibrant arena has become a cornerstone for local sports culture since replacing the Richfield Coliseum. With over 200 events annually, including thrilling basketball games, exciting hockey matches, and captivating concerts, it offers something for everyone.
name: Rocket Arena

excerpt: Opened in 1890, President James A. Garfield's tomb & 180-ft. monument includes an outdoor balcony.
detail_description: The James A. Garfield Monument, located in Lakeview Cemetery, serves as the final resting place and memorial to the 20th President of the United States. Standing at 180 feet tall, this impressive structure features terracotta reliefs depicting significant moments from Garfield's life. The monument includes an outdoor balcony offering panoramic views of its surroundings.
name: James A. Garfield Monument

detail_description: Immerse yourself in the rich holiday traditions and cultural heritage of Cleveland at the Cleveland History Center. Delve into the city's festive celebrations, from early settler customs to grand department store displays, on weekly tours starting December 1. Explore the region's history from its Native American origins to modern times through captivating exhibits featuring a diverse array of artifacts, including a carousel, antique vehicles, and LeBron James' shoe.
name: Cleveland History Center
